items.title: Masterclass in Infection Control (Basic and Advanced)
items.headline: Learn all about infection control from basic to advance level
objectives_summary: Basic and Advanced Infection Prevention and Control Course is aimed to provide understanding about the impact of Hospital Acquired Infections (HAIs) and the roles of various care givers involved in infection prevention and control.  The course incorporates best practices recommended by latest guidelines specially recommended by international agencies like CDC (Centre for disease control and prevention) and IDSA (Infectious disease society of America) on VAP,CLABSI, CAUTI ,SSI etc.  The topics included in this course talk about how and why infections occur in hospitals, common transmission method and ways to break chain of infection. The course also covers the ways of handling biomedical and hazardous wastes and methods of disinfecting the hospital environment.

Speciality of the course: Demonstration of ideal way of doing procedures in hospital starting from catheterization, suctioning, donning and doffing of PPE and various other important procedures to prevent infection in a clinical setup. The course is put forth by, in a simplified and lucid manner without losing its essence.
